<div class=3DWordSection1>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;ms=
o-no-proof:
yes'>Your colonies are the critical element in the game &#8211; they produce
the wealth that powers your empire.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;ms=
o-no-proof:
yes'>Colonies provide tax income to fund your government. However they take=
 time
to grow, so be careful to concentrate your defenses (troops and ships) on y=
our
well-established colonies &#8211; these are the key to your initial growth.=
<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h3><span lang=3DEN-GB>Colonizing new worlds</span></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;ms=
o-no-proof:
yes'>To create new colonies you must build colony ships and send them out to
claim planets for your empire. When a new colony is established the colony =
ship
is consumed and disappears. Note that you can only build colony ships at
colonies with populations of 500 million or more.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;ms=
o-no-proof:
yes'>Colonies can only be established in systems that are not already part =
of
another empire&#8217;s territory.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;ms=
o-no-proof:
yes'>Each alien race has a native planet type that they can colonize at the
start of the game. Research is required to colonize other types of worlds. =
As
your technology levels increase through research you will progressively be =
able
to colonize the following types of planets:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

